Dear Hiring Team, 

It is with great pleasure that I submit my candidacy for the New Grad Software Engineer position with PointOne. I bring over three years of professional experience building novel AI products, RAG pipelines, and serverless systems, along with a strong academic foundation as a Master of Science in Computer Science graduate from Pace University, NY.

Through my experience across two engineering roles, I have built and delivered production-grade AI systems that directly reflect the technical depth and product ownership this position demands. As a Software Engineer at Sperse, I developed novel AI products that translate natural-language intents into safe, validated tool calls across 1,000+ platform endpoints—requiring rigorous API contract design, input validation, and safe execution across distributed systems. I prototyped and integrated retrieval-augmented generation (RAG) workflows to prove out new AI-driven features, working directly with customers to understand their needs and translate them into technical solutions—exactly the kind of customer-facing, high-impact work central to this role. To keep these systems production-ready, I architected a serverless observability layer using Langfuse and LangSmith, covering tracing, structured logging, and evaluation hooks, reducing latency by 60% and LLM API costs by 50% through targeted concurrency and routing optimizations. Prior to Sperse, as a Software Engineer at Qualitest, I built an internal support chatbot using LangChain and RAG with a PostgreSQL vector store, reducing ticket resolution time by 20%—demonstrating my ability to deliver tangible ROI through AI automation. I also developed backend workflows using AWS Step Functions and AWS Lambda (serverless architecture) to handle long-running data import jobs, giving me hands-on experience with the serverless patterns and cloud-native design this role values. Together, these roles have prepared me to contribute meaningfully to PointOne's core engineering responsibilities and drive impact within a rapidly growing team.

My academic research experience has given me a rigorous foundation in AI model development, prototyping, and technical communication—skills that translate directly into the innovation and collaborative culture this team values. As an AI Researcher at the Pace Artificial Intelligence Lab, I conducted research on StyleGAN and Stable Diffusion to generate fashion designs, leveraging CUDA, PyTorch, and LoRA on Pace University's HPC cluster. I was responsible for managing the full model development lifecycle—from training runs to prototyping AI model inference pipelines using vLLM and Hugging Face deployment, ensuring secure and efficient model serving. Beyond building the systems myself, I led workshops on GPU programming with CUDA and Mojo, and on building AI Agents with LangChain and LangGraph, for an audience of 50+ students. Designing and delivering those sessions required me to break down complex technical concepts clearly and accessibly—directly mirroring the mentorship and knowledge-sharing responsibilities central to this role. This experience has shaped me into an engineer who builds with rigor and communicates with clarity, both of which I would bring to PointOne's mission.

I have always been passionate about building best-in-class software tools and solving complex problems that tangibly improve users' lives, and I envision myself contributing my talent to reinventing the business of law through AI infrastructure. I would love to discuss my interest in this position with your team and can be reached at #ph or #eml. Thank you for your time and consideration, I look forward to connecting!

